node.text:
VMU for Velocity Minimum Unstick. This is the absolute minimum speed at which an aircraft can take off and is achieved by pitching the aircraft up to the maximum during the take-off roll.
Wondering what it's like to perform a VMU test? Watch this #TechTuesday episode! ✈️ #airbus #airbuslovers #avgeek #aviationgeek #aviationlovers #instaaviation #plane #instaplane #aerospace #pilot #pilotlife #flighttesting 
📸 H. Goussé

node.title: Flight Tests - Ep.7: Velocity Minimum Unstick

node.text:
When an aircraft takes off or lands on a contaminated runway and depending on the amount of water, the water spray may enter the engine and affect its behaviour.

That’s why our #FlightTest teams put new aircraft through water trough testing to evaluate any risks of water ingestion, primarily by the engines.

Learn more (while staying dry!) in this #TechTuesday episode! ✈️ #airbus #airbuslovers #avgeek #aviationgeek #aviationlovers #instaaviation #plane #instaplane #aerospace #pilot #pilotlife #flighttesting #flighttesting

📸  V. Ricco / DGA Essais en vol

node.title: Flight Tests - Ep.6: Water trough test

node.text:
Do you know why aircraft land like ‘crabs’ during strong crosswinds?
Due to runway configuration and meteorological conditions, there may be crosswind, which the aircraft needs to master at takeoff and landing.
Learn how pilots nail this in this #FlightTest #TechTuesday video. ✈️ #airbus #airbuslovers #avgeek #aviationgeek #aviationlovers #instaaviation #plane #instaplane #aerospace #pilot #pilotlife #flighttesting
📸  A. Tchaikowski

node.text:
A plane may be subject to negative gravity for a very short period.

#FlightTest is carried out to check that the aircraft continues to operate normally and that all systems return to normal quickly when exiting negative-G conditions.

Learn more in today’s #TechTuesday episode. ✈️ #airbus #airbuslovers #avgeek #aviationgeek #aviationlovers #instaaviation #plane #instaplane #aerospace #pilot #pilotlife #flighttesting

📷  S. Ramadier

node.text:
Next up in our #TechTuesday series, we look at how to conduct a development test flight.

With Airbus, there are usually five to six crew members on board: two test pilots, a test flight engineer, and two or three flight test engineers. 👨‍✈️👩‍✈️

Learn more about how the team conducts the tests in this video. ✈️ #airbus #airbuslovers #avgeek #aviationgeek #aviationlovers #instaaviation #plane #instaplane #aerospace #pilot #pilotlife #flighttesting #flighttest

node.text:
The first flight of a new aircraft is always a special moment - it’s when an aircraft comes to life!

It also represents the very first evaluation of the handling characteristics and systems in real flight conditions. It also prepares the start of the #FlightTest campaign by making sure all aircraft systems operate safely to further progress in the flight test campaign.

Enjoy this new #TechTuesday episode and get ready for take-off! ✈️ #airbus #airbuslovers #avgeek #aviationgeek #aviationlovers #instaaviation #plane #instaplane #aerospace #pilot #pilotlife #flighttesting 

📷  S. Ramadier

node.text:
Welcome to the first episode of our #TechTuesday series, a guide to show you some of the key moments of a #FlightTest campaign.

Why are flight tests necessary?

Flight testing is performed to ensure the aircraft complies with certification and safety requirements, and meets operational needs. During the flight test campaign we perform specific certification demonstrations, assess general handling qualities, engines and operational performances, in many specific conditions (cold weather, high altitude airports,...). 
We also check aircraft noise emission and systems operations in real life.

Buckle up and sit back, as you’re in for a ride! ✈️ #airbus #airbuslovers #avgeek #aviationgeek #aviationlovers #instaaviation #plane #instaplane #aerospace #pilot #pilotlife #flighttesting

node.title: Flight Tests - Ep.1: Why flight tests are necessary

VMU for Velocity Minimum Unstick. This is the absolute minimum speed at which an aircraft can take off and is achieved by pitching the aircraft up to the maximum during the take-off roll.
Wondering what it's like to perform a VMU test? Watch this #TechTuesday episode! ✈️ #airbus #airbuslovers #avgeek #aviationgeek #aviationlovers #instaaviation #plane #instaplane #aerospace #pilot #pilotlife #flighttesting 
📸 H. Goussé

node.text:
When an aircraft takes off or lands on a contaminated runway and depending on the amount of water, the water spray may enter the engine and affect its behaviour.

That’s why our #FlightTest teams put new aircraft through water trough testing to evaluate any risks of water ingestion, primarily by the engines.

Learn more (while staying dry!) in this #TechTuesday episode! ✈️ #airbus #airbuslovers #avgeek #aviationgeek #aviationlovers #instaaviation #plane #instaplane #aerospace #pilot #pilotlife #flighttesting #flighttesting

📸  V. Ricco / DGA Essais en vol
